  "intent": "Set up a complete NGS library prep workflow that does three rounds of PCR with cleanup steps between each one. You'll mix up the samples with different PCR reagents, run them on the thermocycler, then clean them up using magnetic beads and ethanol washes. The robot handles all the liquid transfers and bead mixing, and pauses when you need to move plates to the thermocycler. It does the whole thing automatically - adding reagents, mixing, separating the beads with the magnet, washing with ethanol, and resuspending in buffer.",
